{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T17:21:36.457Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Operators combine values into expressions that drive agent decisions: comparing tool latencies, combining boolean guard flags, and building derived configuration. Understanding precedence, short-circuit behavior, and identity versus equality prevents logic bugs in multi-step agent loops."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What it is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "An "}, {"type": "text", "text": "operator", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a symbol that performs an operation on one or more operands. An "}, {"type": "text", "text": "expression", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " is any combination of values, variables, and operators that evaluates to a single value."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Operator categories"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Arithmetic", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "text": "+", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "-", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "*", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "/", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "//", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "%", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "**", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Comparison", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "text": "==", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "!=", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "<", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": ">", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "<=", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": ">=", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Logical", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "text": "and", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "or", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "not", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Membership", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "text": "in", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "not in", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Identity", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "text": "is", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "is not", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Assignment", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "text": "=", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "+=", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": ":=", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " (walrus, Python 3.8+)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why it matters"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Agent control flow depends on expressions: retry while attempts remain, skip tools when budget is exhausted, route to fallback models when confidence is low. A misplaced "}, {"type": "text", "text": "not", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " or confusion between "}, {"type": "text", "text": "==", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "text": "is", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " can send requests down the wrong branch."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefits"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Readable guards", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " — compound conditions encode policy inline"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Short-circuit evaluation", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " — "}, {"type": "text", "text": "and", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " / "}, {"type": "text", "text": "or", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " skip unnecessary work"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Walrus operator", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " — assign and test in one expression, useful in loops parsing streams"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Trade-offs"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Operator precedence", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " — dense expressions without parentheses can surprise readers"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Float comparison", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " — "}, {"type": "text", "text": "0.1 + 0.2 == 0.3", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " is False; use tolerance or "}, {"type": "text", "text": "math.isclose", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " for scores"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Truthy/falsy", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " — empty strings and zero are falsy; explicit comparisons are clearer in agent policy code"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How it works"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Precedence (highest to lowest, simplified)"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Parentheses "}, {"type": "text", "text": "()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Exponentiation "}, {"type": "text", "text": "**", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Unary "}, {"type": "text", "text": "not", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "-", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Multiplication/Division "}, {"type": "text", "text": "*", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "/", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "//", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "%", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Addition "}, {"type": "text", "text": "+", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "-", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Comparisons, membership, identity"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Logical "}, {"type": "text", "text": "not", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "and", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "or", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Identity vs. equality"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "a = [1, 2]\nb = [1, 2]\nc = a\n\na == b   # True — same values\nc is a   # True — same object\na is b   # False — different list objects\n\n# Use == for value comparison\n# Use is for None, singletons, and identity checks only"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Short-circuit logic"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "def expensive_check():\n    print(\"running expensive check\")\n    return True\n\n# Second operand never evaluated if first is False\nFalse and expensive_check()  # prints nothing\n\n# Guard pattern for agent tools\nif tool_enabled and expensive_check():\n    invoke_tool()"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to use it"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use ", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": "==", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " for comparing values"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (strings, numbers, dict contents via equality)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use ", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": "is None", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " for missing optional results"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use ", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": "in", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " for membership"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — checking allowed tool names in a set"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Prefer explicit booleans", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " in agent policy: "}, {"type": "text", "text": "if retries > 0:", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " not "}, {"type": "text", "text": "if retries:", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How to implement"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "MAX_LATENCY_MS = 2000\nattempt = 3\nMAX_ATTEMPTS = 5\n\nshould_retry = (\n    attempt < MAX_ATTEMPTS\n    and latency_ms < MAX_LATENCY_MS\n    and error_code not in FATAL_ERRORS\n)\n\n# Walrus: parse and test in a loop\nwhile (line := log_stream.readline()):\n    if \"ERROR\" in line:\n        handle_error(line)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Examples"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Token budget check\nremaining = max_tokens - used_tokens\ncan_continue = remaining > 0 and not stop_requested\n\n# Chained comparison\n0 <= confidence <= 1.0  # valid Python idiom\n\n# String concatenation vs. addition trap\n\"gpt-\" + model_version   # OK for strings\n# model_version + 1      # TypeError if version is str"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Real-world example"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A router selects a model based on task complexity and cost ceiling:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "COMPLEX = {\"code_review\", \"multi_file_edit\"}\n\ndef select_model(task_type: str, est_tokens: int, budget: float) -> str:\n    if task_type in COMPLEX and est_tokens > 8000:\n        return \"large\"\n    if est_tokens * 0.00001 > budget:\n        return \"small\"\n    return \"medium\""}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common mistakes"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Using ", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": "is", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " for string or int equality"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — CPython may intern small ints, but never rely on "}, {"type": "text", "text": "is", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " for value comparison"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Bitwise vs. logical", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " — "}, {"type": "text", "text": "&", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "text": "|", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " are not "}, {"type": "text", "text": "and", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " / "}, {"type": "text", "text": "or", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Modifying while comparing", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " — changing a list while iterating it (control flow topic)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best practices"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Add parentheses when mixing "}, {"type": "text", "text": "and", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " / "}, {"type": "text", "text": "or", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " for readability"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Extract complex conditions into named booleans: "}, {"type": "text", "text": "within_budget = ...", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use "}, {"type": "text", "text": "math.isclose", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " for float thresholds in scoring and confidence checks"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Comparison with alternatives"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For string building in agent prompts, prefer f-strings (Strings topic) over chained "}, {"type": "text", "text": "+", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " operators — clearer and often faster. For membership tests on large allowlists, use "}, {"type": "text", "text": "set", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " (Collections topic) instead of scanning lists."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mental model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Expressions are small pipelines: operands flow through operators and emerge as a single value. Logical operators are gates — "}, {"type": "text", "text": "and", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " stops at the first False, "}, {"type": "text", "text": "or", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " stops at the first True."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Know precedence; use parentheses when in doubt"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use "}, {"type": "text", "text": "==", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " for values, "}, {"type": "text", "text": "is", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " mainly for "}, {"type": "text", "text": "None", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Short-circuit "}, {"type": "text", "text": "and", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " / "}, {"type": "text", "text": "or", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " enable safe guard patterns"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Agent policy conditions should be explicit and readable"}]}]}]}]}}